This paper deals with modeling and analyzing the interference and coverage probability in underlay device-to-device (D2D) networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and architectures in computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of mathematical tools such as Laplace functional and convergence analysis, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper considers social relationships between D2D nodes, which falls under the category of social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with system-level analysis and optimization, which is related to control and optimization in cyber-physical systems (cs.SY).
